                        <strong>Figure 1</strong><br/>
                                                    &lt;p&gt;Overview of Data Privacy and Model Privacy Attacks in the ML pipeline.&lt;/p&gt;
                                                ">
                    </a>
                                    <a href="https://pub.mdpi-res.com/electronics/electronics-14-01385/article_deploy/html/images/electronics-14-01385-g002.png?1743308194" title="
                        <strong>Figure 2</strong><br/>
                                                    &lt;p&gt;Updated PPFL architecture with institution-specific encryption. This figure highlights how each hospital encrypts patient data locally—using institution-specific cryptographic keys—before sending any information to the Federated Learning Coordinator (FLC). The FLC receives only ciphertext, thus preventing any raw data leaks. The Secure Computation Layer (SCL) applies advanced privacy techniques, while the Compliance and Explainability Module (CEM) provides auditing and interpretability to meet EU AI Act requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
                                                ">
                    </a>
                                    <a href="https://pub.mdpi-res.com/electronics/electronics-14-01385/article_deploy/html/images/electronics-14-01385-g003.png?1743308195" title="
                        <strong>Figure 3</strong><br/>
                                                    &lt;p&gt;UML activity diagram for patient data flow in privacy-preserving healthcare AI. Each step shows how a single patient record is collected, pre-processed, encrypted, and subsequently used for federated model training. The final compliance and auditing phase ensures that privacy regulations are continuously met. Feedback loops allow for risk re-assessment and adaptive cryptographic settings.&lt;/p&gt;
                                                ">
                    </a>
                                    <a href="https://pub.mdpi-res.com/electronics/electronics-14-01385/article_deploy/html/images/electronics-14-01385-g004.png?1743308197" title="
