  <div class="html-fig_description">
    <b>Figure 2.</b>
      Updated PPFL architecture with institution-specific encryption. This figure highlights how each hospital encrypts patient data locally—using institution-specific cryptographic keys—before sending any information to the Federated Learning Coordinator (FLC). The FLC receives only ciphertext, thus preventing any raw data leaks. The Secure Computation Layer (SCL) applies advanced privacy techniques, while the Compliance and Explainability Module (CEM) provides auditing and interpretability to meet EU AI Act requirements.
<!--     <p><a class="html-figpopup" href="#fig_body_display_electronics-14-01385-f002">
      Click here to enlarge figure
    </a></p> -->

  </div>
</div>
<div class="html-fig_show  mfp-hide" id="fig_body_display_electronics-14-01385-f002">
  <div class="html-caption"> <b>Figure 2.</b>
      Updated PPFL architecture with institution-specific encryption. This figure highlights how each hospital encrypts patient data locally—using institution-specific cryptographic keys—before sending any information to the Federated Learning Coordinator (FLC). The FLC receives only ciphertext, thus preventing any raw data leaks. The Secure Computation Layer (SCL) applies advanced privacy techniques, while the Compliance and Explainability Module (CEM) provides auditing and interpretability to meet EU AI Act requirements.</div>
  <div class="html-img"><img data-large="/electronics/electronics-14-01385/article_deploy/html/images/electronics-14-01385-g002.png" data-original="/electronics/electronics-14-01385/article_deploy/html/images/electronics-14-01385-g002.png" alt="Electronics 14 01385 g002" data-lsrc="/electronics/electronics-14-01385/article_deploy/html/images/electronics-14-01385-g002.png" /></div>
